# TigerTix
TigerTix is a ticket-management web application designed to simulate a real-world microservices architecture. 
In Sprint 1, the monolithic starter app was refactored into two independents Node.js/Express microservices â€” Admin Service and Client Service â€” connected through a shared SQLite database, with a React.js frontend consuming live event data. The goal of this sprint was to demonstrate microservice separation, persistent data storage, frontend integration, basic accessibility, and safe concurrent ticket purchases. 

## Prereqs
- Node.js (>= 16)
- npm
